      • HoldingsList

        public HoldingsList(java.sql.Connection connection,
                    java.lang.String seedName,
                    java.lang.String type,
                    java.util.Date start,
                    java.util.Date end)
             throws java.sql.SQLException
        Create a new HoldingsList from a Connection. Optionally restrict the time range for which holdings will be included. seedName, type, start, and end are set, but hostName is not. If start is null, it will be set to the earliest start date retrieved, and if end is null, it will be set to the latest end date retrieved. If start or end is not null, holdings that overlap them will be truncated to fit.
        Parameters:
        connection - The Connection from which to read the holdings
        seedName - Get holdings for the given SEED name
        type - Get holdings for the given type
        start - If not null, do not include holdings that end before this date
        end - If not null, do not include holdings that start after this date
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
